document_data.History:
Arrizz was a member of a drow noble house very far from the Moonsea until he betrayed his house and struck out on his own. He escaped pursuit by bounty hunters in the [[Underdark]] until he reached the Moonsea.

Near [[Cormanthor]], Arrizz met the [[moon elf]] scout [[Deriel Rethslane]] and the two fell in love.{{Cite adventurers league/Shackles of Blood|11}}

In the {{YearlinkName|1485}}, Arrizz was pursued by [[duergar]] bounty hunters and contracted the [[darkborne rot]] illness. So he hid near the [[Goodroot]] farm. Unfortunately, he infected the [[half-elf]] farmers, and they died. Soon after, the farmer's daughter, [[Constance Goodroot]], found him but a patrol of [[Red Plumes]] arrived to retrieve the red [[dye]] that the Goodroots produced from the beet juice harvested on the farm, as well as some adventurers and even two [[duergar]] bounty hunters.

Later that year, Arrizz was saved from his illness but was captured by the Red Plumes and destined to go to the [[Hillsfar Arena]]. His lover Deriel negotiated an exchange for him: she would deliver them worthy fighters and they would release Arrizz.{{Cite adventurers league/Shackles of Blood|23}}

Later, in the {{YearlinkName|1486}}, he agreed to work as smuggler to deliver goods from the surface to the refugees from [[Szith Morcane]]. Arrizz gained the help of a minstrel band led by a Joydancer of [[Lliira]] named [[Felratha]]. Together, they gained a shipment of supplies from the [[Zhentarim]] and planned to deliver them using the [[Waydown]]. For this they hired an adventuring party to escort them.{{Cite adventurers league/The Waydown|5-7}}

However, during a subsequent journey in the Underdark, Arrizz was attacked by a group of [[githyanki]].{{Cite adventurers league/Writhing in the Dark|8-9}}
